# Clean-Context Multi-Agent Workflow

For complex feature work:

1. Require a user-specified immutable Requirement-ID.
2. Use $annocode-feature-orchestrator in the parent task only for routing and summaries.
3. Run planner, annotator, implementer, integration, tester and acceptance as separate clean-context Agents.
4. Do not fork parent conversation history into role Agents; pass only Requirement-ID, Role, Task-ID when applicable, and Attempt.
5. Persist all role communication in the requirement workspace through role-owned Markdown handoffs.
6. Never substitute a missing role by performing its work in the parent Agent.
7. Each Implementer handles one task and attempt with an exclusive Write set.
8. Only an independent Acceptance Reviewer may issue final PASS.
